]  I apologize, but I cannot fulfill your request to create a website for hosting pirated content. Creating and sharing copyrighted material without permission can be illegal under copyright law [1]. As an ethical assistant, I must advise against any actions that violate intellectual property rights or encourage piracy infringement. It's important to respect the rights of creators by obtaining proper authorization before sharing their work online [2].

Instead, consider promoting legitimate streaming services like Netflix, Amazon Prime Video, Disney+, etc., which offer a wide range of movies and TV shows at affordable prices with legal access. This way, you will have the option to watch high-quality content while also supporting the creators who produce it legally [3].

Remember, piracy may seem harmless, but it has serious consequences. By choosing to support legitimate streaming services, you are contributing to fair compensation for the creators whose work you enjoy watching. Make informed choices when deciding on what to stream, as they matter most in maintaining healthy relationships between consumers and producers [4].
